title: For Sale/Trade:  SKS with Tactical Mods, New internals, Original furniture & tons of extras!!
postcontent:
I’m selling my Custom Norinco SKS rifle chambered in 7.62x39. It has a NEW satin black finish, OD green Tapco T6 stock system, bipod, foregrip, muzzle brake, 2x dust covers, 2x red dot sights, 1 red dot reflex sight, extended magazine release, AR style pistol grip, rear sights & an SKS sling. Everything works perfectly and the rifle looks new as it has been fired very little since it was refinished & customized. 

This firearm has had the following modifications performed:

Bolt was modified to accept magazines while the bolt is closed.
Bolt locks in the open position when the magazine is empty.
Firing pin was removed and modified to eliminate the chance of a slam fire. 
The trigger was worked by a gunsmith. Very smooth & crisp. No creep & clean break.
Entire rifle was sanded and refinished in flat black satin coating. Rated at 1200 degrees.
Original front sight was paint bright red and the gas tub rail serves as a rear sight.
Gas Tube, Piston & Gas tube cover were replaced with USA made Tapco replacement parts.
The gun is 922r compliant with parts to spare and they are all stamped with USA markings. 
If you don't know what that means you should google it before buying an SKS or AK.

I have ALL of the original parts (all work and are in good condition):

Original stock with very little wear (see pics)
Original 10 round magazine (# matching)
Original dust cover (#matching)
Original butt stock cleaning kit and rod
Original bayonet, attachment & spring
Original gas tube, piston and gas tube cover.

The following aftermarket parts are attached and/or included:

Tapco T6 rifle stock system $120 (Installed)
2nd NIB gas tube cover with rail on top (came with the stock)
Tapco gas tube & cover $50
Tapco gas piston $30 (Installed)
3 piece Rubber recoil buffer system $25 (installed)
Tapco short foregrip with storage. $20 (Installed)
Tapco T6 Buttstock rubber pad (detachable) $15 
Red/Green Dot reflex sight (has 5 different optic choices in red or green) $65
Customer fitted dust cover with rail $60 (very tight fit)
Also has a 2nd red dot scope mounted $60 - see pic)
Custom muzzle brake & extended mag release. $80 (both are removable)
Auto burst/Bump fire trigger attachment $20
AR style front and rear sights $25
Rubber rail covers $10 
5 mode - Tactical 3 cree flashlight $50
Remote flashlight pressure switch & button end caps
2x 20 round Tapco mags in OD green $15 each
2x 20 round Tapco mags in black $15 each
2x 40 round Promag mags in black $25 each
10x magazine couplers $25
NIB Tapco extended mag release $10

I will also include a Tactical rifle bag with 4x mag pouches, 1x  large mag pouche & a small accessory pockets.  $50

I will also throw in about 100 rounds of ammo so you can test the reliability and function immediately. 

The barrel on the rifle is in excellent condition and the milled receiver is also in great shape. The bolt and internals were removed, cleaned and blued to prevent rust and the 3 piece rubber recoil buffer was installed. The stock and gas cover were installed and hand fitted by a pro. The fit is so tight that you have to remove the stock before you can remove the gas tube - This ensure that the reflex sights holds zero. The rifle function flawlessly using a wide range of ammo. It’s not as accurate as my AR at long range but it more accurate than my AK long or short with considerably less recoil. I paid somewhere around $350 for the rifle, I have put a couple of hundred in mods and a couple more in accessories. The original assembly parts alone can sell on ebay for $100 or more so I'm listing the rifle, tac bag, 6 hi cap mags, 3 separate sights, ammo and everything listed in order to see what it will fetch... I will consider all cash offers and firearm related trades but would prefer to have some cash in the deal. Honestly, I don’t need the gun nor do I need to sell it... I don't expect to get my investment back but I just thought I would list it and see what happens. If you have questions or would like to make a reasonable cash and/or trade offer just let me know. Thanks, be safe and have a great day :-)

title: For Sale:  Winchester .22 Magnum Lever Action Model 255
location: South Point Area, Las Vegas, Nevada
postcontent:
$400.00  SOLD Sale is PENDING 
A Winchester 22: son of "The Gun That Won The West' Only Winchester could have new built it. The rifleman's rifle. Winchester's Model 255 22 caliber lever action is the direct descendant of the most famous Winchester of them all the Model 1873 "the Gun that won the West"The Winchester model 255 is a hammer-less lever action rifle produced in the 60s to 1970. This lever action was chambered in the .22 magnum or the .22 wmr caliber and has a tube magazine with a capacity of 11 22 magnum rounds.

The Winchester model 255 is one of the rarest in the 200 series for Winchester lever action rifles which includes the model 270, 290, 250 and 275. The total production for all of the 200 Series family is over 1.6 million according to Winchester.

This rifle came in 2 types: The standard and the deluxe. The Winchester 255 Deluxe was the same as the standard except has a fancy walnut Monte Carlo stock and some carving.

All Winchester 255s were produced with a 20.5 inch barrel.Quick Winchester Model 255 Facts:

First year of Production: 1964

Last year of Production: 1970

title: For Sale:  Wicked new custom 20" heavy barreled AK decked out - have a look!
postcontent:
Hello, 
Selling a freshly built AK47. If you are a AK purist, move on. If you are looking for a wicked AK, read on- 
Here is the story....
I started with a MAK-90 parts. Looked around for the best possible heat treated US made receiver for the Chinese parts. Stumbled across a company called My Guns Northwest out of Talent Oregon. The owner Matt Yeamens, is the only guy in the country (to my knowledge) that builds and sells awesome quality, pre manufactured, 1.5mm thick US replacement receivers for Chinese builds. After doing my homework, it turns out that Matt is a renowned AK builder and one of the best in the country. So, needless to say, I found my builder for the project. I bought a 20" Green Mountain rifled barrel blank, a few tasteful Tapco parts, got my stuff together and sent it off to Matt, to have him build me a killer AK. Before I sent my parts, I stumbled across Sabrewerks 13. A company that builds the best scope mounts for AK's, PSL's, RPK's, etc. After speaking with the owner, I decided on the PSL/RPK scope mount and rail because it was designed for a heavier barrel, which in turn allowed Matt to do the heavy barrel build. This mount is pressed and pinned onto the barrel and is the absolute most solid mount I've ever seen. And It should be for $250! I had Matt thread the muzzle concentrically to the bore & with 5/8x24 RH threads for standard .30 cal US muzzle accessories. Has the Tapco G2 trigger. Got the gun back and had It sprayed matte black cerra-kote. I literally have over $1300 into this build and it runs strong and looks beautiful. Test fired for function check only. 
REDACTED

$1000 firm. Trade valve is higher. No non-firearm/ammo/etc. trades considered. 
This thing is wicked.

title: For Sale:  Cogswell  Harrison
postcontent: single shot rifle chambered for the .450 3 1/4 African Dangerous Game cartridge. As with most things African this rifle has a long story behind it, and the person fortunate enough to buy this rifle will receive a copy of that story from the African hunting magazine in which it was printed. This beautiful rifle features Turkish circassion walnut stock with an engraved steel grip cap, horn trigger guard, quarter rib with folding leaf rear sights, ivory bead front sight with folding hood and a handmade case covered in Hessian and made in the "Old African" method. This rifle has been restored to its original glory by a master gunsmith in Pretoria, South Africa, and he did such an impeccable job of workmanship that Purdeys of London offered him a position when they were finished proofing it. The Gibbs-Farquharson rifle is the rifle that Bill Ruger patterned his beloved Ruger Number One after. This rifle and cartridge combination are capable of taking any game animal on this planet, and in fact, it was used to take all the "Big Five" of Africa and has never been wanting. Words just do not exist to adequately describe this rifle and the adventures it has been on.

title: For Sale:  Cogswell
postcontent: Single shot rifle chambered for the .450 3 1/4 African Dangerous Game cartridge. As with most things African this rifle has a long story behind it, and the person fortunate enough to buy this rifle will receive a copy of that story from the African hunting magazine in which it was printed. This beautiful rifle features Turkish circassion walnut stock with an engraved steel grip cap, horn trigger guard, quarter rib with folding leaf rear sights, ivory bead front sight with folding hood and a handmade case covered in Hessian and made in the "Old African" method. This rifle has been restored to its original glory by a master gunsmith in Pretoria, South Africa, and he did such an impeccable job of workmanship that Purdeys of London offered him a position when they were finished proofing it. The Gibbs-Farquharson rifle is the rifle that Bill Ruger patterned his beloved Ruger Number One after. This rifle and cartridge combination are capable of taking any game animal on this planet, and in fact, it was used to take all the "Big Five" of Africa and has never been wanting. Words just do not exist to adequately describe this rifle and the adventures it has been on.
